        parsed_args={
            'final_result': '## Mapping Grok\'s Disclosed Offerings onto a B2C-to-B2B Monetization Ladder\n\nBased on the SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026), Grok\'s offerings can be mapped onto a six-rung monetization ladder, ascending from free consumer access to government/sovereign deployment:\n\n### Rung 1 — Free/Freemium Consumer (B2C)\n- **Grok Chat** (conversational interface), **Grok Imagine** (image/video generation), **Grok Voice** (real-time speech)\n- Distribution: grok.com, mobile apps, X platform, xAI API\n- ~117M MAUs using Grok\'s AI features (as of 3/31/2026); ~550M total MAUs\n\n### Rung 2 — Paid Consumer Subscriptions (B2C)\n- Tiers: **Basic, SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy, SuperGrok Lite**; plus X **Premium/Premium+**\n- ~6.3M total active paid subscribers (4.4M X Premium/Premium+ + 1.9M SuperGrok-family) as of 3/31/2026\n- Pricing assumptions (for TAM): $30/mo high-income, $8/mo middle-income, lower in low-income; weighted avg ~$12/mo\n- Future intent: introduce advertising into standalone Grok\n\n### Rung 3 — Developer/API Access (B2B-adjacent)\n- **Grok API**: programmatic access to Grok models (reasoning, vision, tool-use, image gen, voice, real-time search)\n- Pricing: stand-ready access (ratable) or usage-based (as consumed); contract terms month-to-month up to one year\n- **No revenue figure, customer count, or usage metrics disclosed**\n\n### Rung 4 — SMB/Team Enterprise (B2B)\n- **Grok Teams**: dedicated workspaces, secure sharing, admin controls, data not used for training\n- **Grok Business**: subscription-based access for internal workflows\n- Pricing: license-, consumption-, or outcome-based\n- **No customer count, ARR, or revenue disclosed**\n\n### Rung 5 — Large Enterprise (B2B)\n- **Grok Enterprise**: larger-scale deployment, same pricing models\n- Go-to-market intent: "specialized salesforce and forward deployed engineers"\n- Only named external partner: **Cursor** (compute agreement + option agreement; implied Cursor equity value $60B